 "body": "<div><p><span><span>The </span><span>‘offset’ or ‘cove</span><span>r’ method applies to companies which have adopted SSAP 20 </span></span><span><span>Foreign Currency Translation </span></span><span><span>under old UK GAAP.</span> </span><span><span>Its use is subject to certain conditions, which are discussed at</span> </span><span><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/hmrc-internal-manuals/corporate-finance-manual/cfm26130\"><span>CFM2</span><span>6130</span></a></span><span><span>.</span></span>&nbsp;</p></div>\n<div><p><span><span>See </span></span><span><span><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/hmrc-internal-manuals/corporate-finance-manual/cfm26140\">CFM26140</a></span></span><span><span> for an example of the use of </span><span>this</span><span> method.</span></span>&nbsp;</p></div>\n",
